      "writtenOn": "2021-04-23T20:40:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "shouldn\u0027t this be a real regexp check? What if mode_regexp is [\"A.A.Y.ER_RUN\"]?\n\n`mode_regexp` is a weird API...",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 285,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 285,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "8a9286e50978016b07f0970df45dad8156e1db8e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6a01d488_cf05cbe1",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/rules/cq_tryjob_verifier.star",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 285,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-26T18:00:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I had a chat with Vadim about this.\nVadim\u0027s point: regexp is very powerful and perhaps we shouldn\u0027t be using it if a weaker way to filter modes will suffice, and then checks like these ought to be easier. For example, https://github.com/google/cel-spec can be considered.\n\nMy take is:\n 1. we don\u0027t have time to design less powerful API right now.\n 2. the scalar mode will probably not suffice anyway in the future, and we\u0027ll have to do some kind of migration anyway (e.g. from scalar to struct {name, when\u003d{upload|lgtm|etc}, what\u003d{tryjobs-only|submit|etc}}).\n   -\u003e 2.1. (counter): in this case, disallowing regexps will make things easier, as it\u0027d allow us to potentially automate the migration, while regexps would require human intervention.\n\n\nYiwei/Vadim: WDYT about s/mode_regexp/mode, which would require enumerations. I think we can break backwards compat *today* because nobody except cq-test project is using it.\n\nFor *this* CL though, the code as it stands is OK, IMO.",
      "parentUuid": "ecf017e7_f0bebdde",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 285,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 285,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "8a9286e50978016b07f0970df45dad8156e1db8e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
